# Archive

Older versions of corpus documents. The canonical (latest) version of each file lives in the main directory under its suffix-less name; older versions are preserved here with their sequential version number for the record.

Files are named: `[number]-[Title]-v[N].docx` — where the version number reflects WHICH content iteration the file represents, not the order it was archived.

The visible archive lets future readers see the progression of the work without needing git knowledge. Git itself preserves full commit history regardless.
